"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-12-best-memes-paris-2024-olympic-ceremonies-21405877\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"TheParis 2024 Olympic Gameshas officially wrapped up, following a closing ceremony that saw the event get a Hollywood ending.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999878667426251, \"rank\": 1.2133404465566202e-05, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike the opening ceremony, whichtook place outside the stadiumand on the River Seine, the Games ended in the Stade deFrance- with the likes ofTom Cruise, Red Hot Chili Peppers,Billie Eilish,Snoop Doggand Dr Dre taking part in the spectacle.\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 202, \"end\": 213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Billie Eilish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, as usual, social media users were quick to share their reactions online.\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From big moments likeTom Cruise's hair-raising stuntsto awkward fumbles including aman eating noodles on stageand aTeam GB flag bearer almost tripping over, there was plenty to talk about.\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 569, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999891797832463, \"rank\": 1.0818273702141393e-05, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One moment that caught user's attention was Leon Marchand's farewell.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999849792404, \"rank\": 1.0964698142379992e-08, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Olympian was a standout star at the Games, winning four gold medals and one bronze.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 714, \"end\": 720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8918648563493504, \"rank\": 0.0619901132731001, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999218353, \"rank\": 4.001818666860529e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So it was fitting that he brought the Paris Games to a close - but social media users saw the funny side as he carried a small Olympic torch towards the Louvre.\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 959, \"end\": 965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9999999825595297, \"rank\": 1.7440445396687773e-08, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wi